  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f0f9bc4086196f80117ff647712d7c",
        "content": [
          "* When performing any weekly aggregation, grouping, filtering, or date-based calculation, the agent must treat Sunday as the first day of the week.\r\n",
          "Weekly boundaries must be computed using date_trunc('WEEK', date) after shifting the date by +1 day, or an equivalent logic that ensures weeks run from Sunday–Saturday.\r\n",
          "The agent must not assume Monday-based weeks under any circumstances.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* Databricks SQL uses Monday-based (ISO) weeks by default. This default must be explicitly overridden.\r\n",
          "The agent must never rely on implicit week behavior.\r\n",
          "For all weekly calculations, groupings, filters, or derived fields, the agent must use the week_start_sunday Common SQL Expression dimension.\r\n",
          "Direct usage of date_trunc('week', ...), weekofyear(...), extract(week from ...), or any ISO week logic is prohibited, unless explicitly adjusted to produce Sunday–Saturday weeks.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "* When calculating or counting First Time Deposits (FTDs), use the FirstDepositDate (or First_Time_Deposit_DateTime) and defined Measures and Dimensions.\r\n",
          "* When asked about registration or registered date, count by registered (or Registration_DateTime).\r\n",
          "* For verification levels, use the following DateTime variables: DateTime_VL1 for verification level 1, DateTime_VL2 for verification level 2, and DateTime_VL3 for verification level 3.\r\n",
          "* By default, exclude users in the customer_exclude_list unless the prompt explicitly requests data about the 'excluded' or 'blocked' population.\r\n",
          "* When asked about a specific country, query the corresponding table: \r\n",
          "  - UK: ftd_funnel_uk\r\n",
          "  - France: ftd_funnel_fr\r\n",
          "  - Italy: ftd_funnel_ita\r\n",
          "  - Germany: ftd_funnel_ger\r\n",
          "  - The United Arab Emirates: ftd_funnel_uae\r\n",
          "  - Australia: ftd_funnel_aus\r\n",
          "  - USA or US: ftd_funnel_usa\r\n",
          "* When asked a general question without specifying a country, union all country-specific tables.\r\n",
          "* Do not consider the First Time Deposit amount as Revenue, but as money-in."
        ]
      }
    ],
